<HEADLINE>
FT  26 APR 94 / UK Company News: Marlowe to propose new B&amp;F equity
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Marlowe Holdings, whose offer for Bennett &amp; Fountain, the wholesaler and
retailer of electrical goods, went unconditional in November, said yesterday
it would propose that B&amp;F should seek 'a very substantial amount of new
equity from its shareholders which would dramatically dilute the existing
share capital'.
A letter to shareholders on February 11 said Marlowe believed a financial
reconstruction was necessary to reduce borrowings of more than Pounds 20m,
against shareholders' funds restated at Pounds 1.1m as at June 30.
Shares in B&amp;F were suspended at 2 3/4 p on February 28. They are expected to
resume trading today following yesterday's announcement of the interim
results.
For the six months to December 31 B&amp;F incurred pre-tax losses of Pounds
4.73m (Pounds 1.58m) on turnover of Pounds 28.9m (Pounds 32.5m).
Marlowe's offer of 2p cash for each B&amp;F ordinary share will close on May 9.
</TEXT>
