FT  26 APR 94 / People: Royal Bank of Scotland
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Jeff Thornton, a high-flying Scottish civil servant, is leaving the Scottish
Office to join Royal Bank of Scotland, where he is to set up a specialist
group to assemble private finance for public sector projects.
Thornton is currently head of industrial policy and technology at the
Scottish Office. He has been private secretary to Malcolm Rifkind, formerly
