which aims to find private money for projects such as bridges, railways,
sewage works and hospitals. Scotland, with a second Forth road bridge on the
drawing board and plans to involve the private sector in the water and
sewerage industry, is a key area.
Thornton is yet another recruit to the Royal Bank who has previously worked
with Mathewson at the now defunct Scottish Development Agency. He was
assistant to Mathewson when the latter was the SDA's ceo in the 1980s.
Others in this category are Iain Robertson, Mathewson's successor as the
SDA's chief executive, who now runs the bank's corporate and institutional
banking, and Frank Kirwan, director of retail banking services. Kirwan was
previously head of strategy at the bank, and earlier at the SDA.
