FT  26 APR 94 / Report backs new qualifications
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
New competence-based qualifications can act as a device for motivating staff
at various levels in the financial services industries according to a report
published today.
The report, which includes case studies, was prepared by the Financial
Services Lead Bodies Group, which was partly responsible for developing
National Vocational Qualifications for its sector.
Ms Liz Chiswell, one of the authors of the case studies, said a number of
teething problems with NVQs remained, but there were business benefits to be
had from the qualifications.
