FT  25 APR 94 / Letters to the Editor: Russian courtesy
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr P N SOLARES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Efficiency and helpfulness are not the west's usual view of Russians.
Nevertheless, my experience last week in St Petersburg certainly had traits
of both.
The night before travelling back to London I realised that I had lost my air
ticket. Next morning I went to have the ticket replaced at the hotel travel
agent. The agent phoned KLM and was told that the Hermitage Museum had
reported that a ticket with my name on it had been found in the coat check
area and was being held for me at the museum. I went to retrieve the ticket
with the aid of a taxi driver who accompanied me all the way into the
administration area of the museum. The whole process took about
three-quarters of an hour.
I doubt museum staff and taxi drivers in western cities would have bothered.
P N Solares,
senior vice-president,
