<HEADLINE>
FT  25 APR 94 / Philby widow to auction his hat
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The Russian widow of Soviet spy Kim Philby hopes to raise money to
supplement her KGB pension by selling his books, papers, homburg hat, Cuban
cigars and cocktail shaker.
Mrs Rufina Philby, 61, the British-born spy's fourth wife, has put the
contents of his library and other items found in his Moscow flat after his
death in 1988 into an auction at Sotheby's on July 18.
Philby defected to the Soviet Union in 1963 after passing information from
British intelligence to the KGB for 24 years.
It emerged that he was the 'third man' after Guy Burgess and Donald Maclean
to penetrate western intelligence.
Philby's hat is expected to fetch up to Pounds 3,000, his camera Pounds
1,000, his Russian watch Pounds 700 and his cocktail shaker Pounds 500.
