<HEADLINE>
FT  25 APR 94 / World News in Brief: European Monetary System
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The German, Belgian, French, Spanish and Portuguese central banks trimmed
interest rates last week, but the EMS grid remained almost unchanged. The
Irish punt remains the strongest currency, with the two Iberian currencies
at the bottom. Currencies, Page 33 The chart shows the member currencies of
the exchange rate mechanism measured against the weakest currency in the
system. Most of the currencies are permitted to fluctuate within 15 per cent
of agreed central rates against the other members of the mechanism. The
exceptions are the D-Mark and the guilder which move in a 2.25 per cent
band.
